<docs>
	<doc for="ImageClickEventHandler">
		<summary>
			<para>Represents the method that will handle any events that are
      raised when a user clicks on an image-based ASP.NET server control.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="sender">The server control that is the source of the event.</param>
		<param name=" e">An <see cref="System.Web.UI.ImageClickEventArgs"/> object that contains event data.</param>
		<remarks>
			<para>This delegate defines the required signature for all
      click events raised when a user clicks on an image-based ASP.NET server control.
      You must use the signature defined by this delegate for any
   <see langword="OnServerClick"/> event handlers that you create for
      an <see cref="System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlInputImage"/> server control or any
   <see langword="OnClick"/> event handlers that you create for an <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.ImageButton"/> Web server control.</para>
			<para>If you create a custom image-based ASP.NET server
      control that users can click, use this delegate to define the events
      associated with that user action. For more information, see <see topic="cpcondefiningcustomevent"/>. </para>
			<para>For more information about delegates and how they
      interact with events, see <see topic="cpconeventsdelegates"/>. For information about how to raise events,
      see <see topic="cpconprovidingeventfunctionality"/>.</para>
		</remarks>
